<section class="py-20 bg-gradient-to-b from-trueno-black-light to-trueno-black">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <!-- Main card -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-trueno-black-muted/80 to-trueno-black border border-trueno-white-dark/10 rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-12 relative" data-aos="fade-up">
        <!-- Decorative elements -->
        <div class="absolute -right-8 top-0 text-8xl opacity-5 rotate-12 transform-gpu">⚡</div>
        <div class="absolute -left-12 bottom-0 text-9xl opacity-5 -rotate-12 transform-gpu">⚡</div>
        
        <div class="relative z-10">
          <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl font-racing mb-6 text-trueno-white
            [text-shadow:_4px_4px_8px_rgb(0_0_0_/_85%)]">
            <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-4">
              <span class="text-3xl transform-gpu hover:rotate-12 transition-transform duration-300">⚡</span>
              <span class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2">
                The 
                <span>Power</span>
                <span>of</span>
                <span class="text-trueno-red [text-shadow:_0.5px_0.5px_0_#000,_1px_1px_4px_rgb(0_0_0_/_30%)]">Thunder</span>
              </span>
            </div>
          </h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-6 text-base sm:text-lg text-trueno-white-muted">
            <p>
              Did you know? The name <span class="font-racing text-xl tracking-[0.15em] text-trueno-red
                [text-shadow:_0.5px_0.5px_0_#000,_1px_1px_4px_rgb(0_0_0_/_30%)]">Trueno</span> means "thunder" in Spanish – 
              a fitting name for a car that roared into history as a lightweight, agile icon.
            </p>
            
            <p>
              Toyota paired it with its sibling, the <span class="font-racing text-xl tracking-[0.15em] text-trueno-white">Levin</span> (meaning "lightning"), 
              to create a dynamic duo of speed and style. The Trueno, with its iconic pop-up headlights, 
              became the star of the AE86 lineup – and later, the hero car of <em>Initial D</em>, where it 
              cemented its legacy as the ultimate underdog.
            </p>

            <p class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-racing text-trueno-red
              [text-shadow:_0.5px_0.5px_0_#000,_1px_1px_4px_rgb(0_0_0_/_30%)]">
              Now, that same legendary design is here to bring thunder to your key organization.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  @keyframes shine {
    from {
      transform: translateX(-100%);
    }
    to {
      transform: translateX(100%);
    }
  }

  .animate-shine {
    animation: shine 2s infinite;
    mask-image: linear-gradient(to right, transparent, white, transparent);
  }
</style>